  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Mortgage Specialist (Sales Executive)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>🏡 We’re Hiring: Mortgage Specialist! 🏡</strong></h3>\n<p>Are you passionate about <strong>helping clients achieve their homeownership dreams</strong>? Join our team as a <strong>Mortgage Specialist</strong> and be a key player in guiding customers through their home financing journey!</p>\n<h3><strong>🔹 Job Responsibilities:</strong></h3>\n<p>✅ <strong>Provide Mortgage Solutions</strong> – Advise clients on home loan options, refinancing, and mortgage planning.<br>\n✅ <strong>Assess Client Needs</strong> – Analyze financial profiles to recommend the best mortgage solutions.<br>\n✅ <strong>Manage Loan Applications</strong> – Assist clients in preparing and submitting mortgage applications.<br>\n✅ <strong>Build Strong Relationships</strong> – Work closely with banks, financial institutions, and real estate agents.<br>\n✅ <strong>Stay Updated</strong> – Keep up with mortgage rates, regulations, and market trends.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔹 What We’re Looking For:</strong></h3>\n<p>✔️ <strong>Strong communication &amp; financial advisory skills</strong> – Ability to explain mortgage options clearly.<br>\n✔️ <strong>Sales-driven &amp; target-oriented</strong> – Passionate about achieving financial goals.<br>\n✔️ <strong>Experience in mortgage advisory, banking, or finance is a plus.</strong><br>\n✔️ <strong>Detail-oriented &amp; analytical</strong> – Able to assess financial documents and loan structures.<br>\n✔️ <strong>Self-motivated &amp; independent</strong> – Can work autonomously while meeting client needs.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔹 What We Offer:</strong></h3>\n<p>✨ <strong>Attractive commission &amp; incentive structure</strong><br>\n✨ <strong>Training &amp; professional development</strong><br>\n✨ <strong>Supportive team &amp; mentorship program</strong><br>\n✨ <strong>Career growth opportunities in the financial industry</strong></p>\n<p>🎯 <strong>Ready to help clients secure their dream homes? Join us today!</strong></p>",
